      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Zurich Card"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After we checked into our hotel, the first thing we did was go back to the main train station to pick up our 24-hour "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://www.zuerich.com/en/visit/your-city-travel-pass",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Zurich Card"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". For about $25 per person, this card includes all Zurich public transportation and entrance to most of the city's museums for 24 hours. We did the math and decided it was worth it for us. They also offer a 72-hour pass for a great deal if you are planning to stay in the city for at least three days."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Viaduct Market Hall"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After picking up our Zurich Cards, we wanted to just wander the city, but we were also starving. We had eaten some grocery store food we brought on the boat with us, but we were ready for another snack. We read about the Viaduct Market Hall and thought it sounded perfect since it was indoor and would be a way for us to access some cheaper, local snacks. It ended up being one of the nicest indoor markets I've ever been to! The vendors were all local farmers, butchers, bakers, etc. It wasn't crowded at all, and we were able to select a couple of affordable snacks and Swiss drinks after looking through all that the Swiss vendors and shops had to offer."
          }
        ]
      },
